3:["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["How Funding Works on ","Drift"]}]
4:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Drift calculates funding rates every hour using a time-weighted average of the premium between perpetual and index prices. The hybrid vAMM-DLOB system ensures funding rates closely track spot-perp basis, with JIT (Just-In-Time) liquidity auctions providing additional price stability during volatile periods. Funding payments occur automatically at each hourly interval, with rates displayed as 1-hour percentages. Long positions pay funding when rates are positive, while short positions collect funding, creating natural arbitrage incentives for traders to balance market positioning."}]
5:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","SUI","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"SUI's positioning as a next-generation Layer 1 blockchain generates significant speculative interest, leading to pronounced funding rate imbalances during trend periods. The token's mid-tier trading volume provides sufficient liquidity for arbitrage strategies while maintaining enough volatility to generate meaningful funding premiums. SUI's correlation with broader L1 narratives and developer activity creates predictable funding patterns around ecosystem announcements and network upgrades."}]]}]
6:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical SUI Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"SUI funding rates on Drift have exhibited distinct patterns tied to network development milestones and Layer 1 sector rotation. During bull runs, positive funding rates often exceed 0.1% hourly as retail interest drives perpetual premiums above spot prices. Bear market periods typically see negative funding rates averaging -0.02% to -0.05% hourly as short interest dominates. The 1-hour funding cycle amplifies these patterns, creating 24 distinct arbitrage opportunities daily compared to traditional 8-hour systems. Seasonal patterns emerge around Move programming language adoption and DeFi protocol launches on Sui Network."}]]}]
7:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities and Execution"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Drift's low maker fees (0.02%) and Solana's sub-second transaction finality enable high-frequency funding rate strategies on SUI/USDT. The vAMM component provides immediate liquidity for large positions, while DLOB orders can capture precise entry/exit points around funding timestamps. Cross-exchange arbitrage between Drift and centralized platforms becomes viable due to minimal slippage and fast settlement. JIT liquidity auctions during volatile periods can create additional alpha through temporary price dislocations. Insurance fund protections reduce counterparty risk compared to under-collateralized DeFi alternatives."}]]}]
8:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Management and Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Solana network dependency represents the primary systematic risk, as network congestion or outages can prevent timely position adjustments around funding intervals. SUI's relatively shorter price history increases volatility unpredictability compared to established assets like BTC or ETH. Drift's complex liquidation mechanics involving partial liquidations and backstop AMM can create unexpected slippage during adverse moves. Lower overall liquidity versus major centralized exchanges may result in wider spreads during market stress. Smart contract risks inherent to DeFi protocols require additional due diligence compared to regulated exchanges."}]]}]
9:["$","$Le",null,{"items":[{"question":"How does Drift's 1-hour funding compare to other exchanges for SUI arbitrage?","answer":"Drift's hourly funding intervals provide 24x more arbitrage opportunities than exchanges using 8-hour cycles, allowing for more precise risk management and faster capital turnover. However, this requires more active monitoring and may increase transaction costs through frequent position adjustments."},{"question":"What makes SUI funding rates more volatile than established cryptocurrencies?","answer":"SUI's newer market presence and smaller market cap create higher susceptibility to narrative-driven speculation and whale movements. Layer 1 tokens also experience concentrated funding pressure during sector rotation events and network upgrade cycles."},{"question":"How does Drift's vAMM-DLOB hybrid model affect SUI funding rate accuracy?","answer":"The hybrid model improves funding rate precision by combining vAMM liquidity with DLOB price discovery, reducing artificial premiums/discounts that can skew funding calculations. JIT auctions provide additional stability during volatile periods when funding rates matter most."},{"question":"What Solana network risks should SUI funding arbitrageurs consider?","answer":"Network congestion during high TPS periods can delay critical trades around funding timestamps. Validator issues or network restarts may prevent position management, creating exposure to unhedged funding payments. Maintaining backup strategies on alternative networks is advisable for large positions."}]}]
